Appendix E: Worked Risk & Exit Example  
Account size: $100,000  
Risk per trade: 1% = $1,000 max loss  
Trailing stop: 4% (trails from intraday high after scale-out; remaining position continues to run until stop hit or EOD close)  
Position size = $1,000 / 0.04 = $25,000 (25% of account)  
Entry price: $50/share → 500 shares  
If price reaches $60 (+20%), trailing stop moves to $57.60 (4% below high)  
If price reverses to $57.60 → exit at $57.60 → profit = ($57.60 – $50) × 500 = $3,800  
Level 3 example: Scale out 50% (250 shares) at +10–12% ($55–$56) → lock $1,250–$1,500 profit; trail remaining 250 shares with 4% stop.

